cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with segmentation, tracking, and reconstruction of 3D shapes from RGB-D images. It also involves object-level scene understanding, which is a common topic in computer vision research. 

The paper also involves robotics (cs.RO) as it aims to enable a robot to interact with its working environment by maintaining a scene description at the object level. 

Machine learning (cs.LG) is another likely sub-category as the paper uses a multiple model fitting approach to track and fuse the 3D shapes of multiple objects. 

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves developing a system that can understand and interact with its environment. 

Finally, computer graphics (cs.GR) is a less likely sub-category as the paper involves 3D shape reconstruction, which is a common topic in computer graphics research.
